es and collective norms after the destabilisation of war.Through an interdisciplinary lens, this collection analyses the depiction of these transgressive figures in a variety of visual media, as well as the narrative, socio-cultural, political and historical contexts in which they emerge.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMilitary deserters in motion pictures. 0aWar filmsxHistory and criticism. 0aWar films-History and criticism. 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aHISTORY / Military / Wars & Conflicts (Other).2bisacsh1 aBjerre, Thomas Ærvold, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDolgoy, Rebecca Clare, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHanna, Emma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMajor, Patrick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPiotrowska, Agnieszka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPurse, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSternberg, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWestwell, Guy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWölfel, Ute, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWölfel, Ute, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311078041340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147444628040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474446280423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474446280/original  a978-3-11-078041-3  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aE